{"type":"message","id":"afc80896","parentId":"6db5f2d7","timestamp":"2026-03-07T06:51:46.675Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a19dbe0e96434f8db374e22c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Signal Group Calendar System — Design Document\n\n**Author:** Temujin (Developer)\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**Status:** Design Complete — Ready for Implementation\n**Source:** danny_directive\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nA calendar/event system for Danny's Signal friend group. Members send natural language messages (\"Dinner at Mario's Friday 7pm\") and the system parses, stores, queries, and sends reminders for events — all via Signal.\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\nSignal Group Chat\n       |\n  signal-cli (JSON-RPC)\n       |\n  calendar_handler.py         # Message intake + routing\n       |\n  +---------+---------+\n  |                   |\n  parse_event.py      query_events.py\n  (LLM + dateparser)  (Neo4j Cypher)\n       |\n  neo4j_calendar.py           # Graph CRUD\n       |\n  Neo4j (bolt://localhost:7687)\n       |\n  reminder_worker.py          # Cron: check due reminders, send via signal-cli\n```\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- Single LLM call (Claude Haiku via OpenRouter, ~$0.45/month) for intent classification + entity extraction\n- `dateparser` library for deterministic date/time resolution\n- Neo4j for event storage with fulltext search for fuzzy matching\n- Person nodes separate from existing Agent nodes, bridged via OPERATES_AS\n\n---\n\n## 2. Neo4j Schema\n\n### 2.1 Constraints\n\n```cypher\n-- Person: phone_number is primary key (E.164 format)\nCREATE CONSTRAINT person_phone_unique IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (p:Person) REQUIRE p.phone_number IS UNIQUE;\n\n-- Person: Signal UUID for future-proofing\nCREATE CONSTRAINT person_signal_id_unique IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (p:Person) REQUIRE p.signal_id IS UNIQUE;\n\n-- Event: UUID-based ID\nCREATE CONSTRAINT event_id_unique IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (e:Event) REQUIRE e.event_id IS UNIQUE;\n\n-- Location: deduplicated by normalized name\nCREATE CONSTRAINT location_name_unique IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (l:Location) REQUIRE l.name_key IS UNIQUE;\n\n-- Reminder: UUID-based ID\nCREATE CONSTRAINT reminder_id_unique IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (r:Reminder) REQUIRE r.reminder_id IS UNIQUE;\n\n-- RecurrenceSeries: UUID-based ID\nCREATE CONSTRAINT series_id_unique IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (s:RecurrenceSeries) REQUIRE s.series_id IS UNIQUE;\n```\n\n### 2.2 Indexes\n\n```cypher\n-- Primary query: \"what's coming up?\" - range scan on start_datetime\nCREATE INDEX event_start_idx IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (e:Event) ON (e.start_datetime);\n\n-- Filter active/cancelled\nCREATE INDEX event_status_idx IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (e:Event) ON (e.status);\n\n-- Person lookup by name (\"add Liz to dinner\")\nCREATE INDEX person_name_idx IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (p:Person) ON (p.name);\n\n-- Reminder cron: find unsent reminders due now\nCREATE INDEX reminder_due_idx IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (r:Reminder) ON (r.remind_at);\n\nCREATE INDEX reminder_sent_idx IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (r:Reminder) ON (r.sent);\n\n-- Fulltext for fuzzy event search (\"next dinner\", \"that brunch thing\")\nCREATE FULLTEXT INDEX event_search IF NOT EXISTS\nFOR (e:Event) ON EACH [e.name, e.description];\n```\n\n### 2.3 Node Types\n\n| Label | Primary Key | Properties |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| **Person** | `phone_number` | signal_id, name, aliases[], role (\"admin\"/\"member\"), active, created_at, updated_at |\n| **Event** | `event_id` | name, description, start_datetime, end_datetime, all_day, status (\"active\"/\"cancelled\"/\"completed\"), visibility, source_message, created_at, updated_at |\n| **Location** | `name_key` | name, address, latitude, longitude, created_at |\n| **Reminder** | `reminder_id` | remind_at, offset_desc, sent, sent_at, channel, created_at |\n| **RecurrenceSeries** | `series_id` | rrule, frequency, day_of_week, until, created_at |\n\n### 2.4 Relationships\n\n```\n(Event)-[:CREATED_BY {created_at}]->(Person)\n(Person)-[:ATTENDING {rsvp, rsvp_at, added_by}]->(Event)\n(Event)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(Location)\n(Reminder)-[:REMINDER_FOR]->(Event)\n(Reminder)-[:REMIND]->(Person)\n(Event)-[:INSTANCE_OF {instance_index}]->(RecurrenceSeries)\n(Person)-[:OPERATES_AS]->(Agent)   -- bridge to existing Kurultai schema\n```\n\n### 2.5 Graph Topology\n\n```\n                +---------+\n                |  Agent  |  (existing Kurultai)\n                +----^----+\n                     | OPERATES_AS\n                +----+----+\n    +-----------| Person  |------------+\n    |           +----+----+            |\n    | REMIND         | ATTENDING       | CREATED_BY (reverse)\n    |                | (rsvp)          |\n+---v------+   +-----v-----+    +-----+-----+\n| Reminder |   |           |    |           |\n+---+------+   |   Event   |    |   Event   |\n    |          |           |    |           |\n    |          +--+----+---+    +-----------+\n    | REMINDER_FOR|    | AT_LOCATION\n    +-------------+    |\n                  +----v-----+\n                  | Location |\n                  +----------+\n\n                  | INSTANCE_OF\n                  v\n           +----------------+\n           |RecurrenceSeries|\n           +----------------+\n```\n\n### 2.6 Seed Data\n\n```cypher\n-- Bootstrap group members (run once, MERGE is idempotent)\nMERGE (p:Person {phone_number: \"+19194133445\"})\nON CREATE SET p.name = \"Danny\", p.role = \"admin\", p.active = true,\n              p.created_at = datetime(), p.updated_at = datetime();\n\nMERGE (p:Person {phone_number: \"+16624580725\"})\nON CREATE SET p.name = \"Liz\", p.role = \"member\", p.active = true,\n              p.created_at = datetime(), p.updated_at = datetime();\n\n-- Link Danny to existing Kublai Agent (if desired)\nMATCH (p:Person {phone_number: \"+19194133445\"})\nMATCH (a:Agent {name: \"kublai\"})\nMERGE (p)-[:OPERATES_AS]->(a);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Event Intake Flow (Message -> Parsed Event -> Neo4j)\n\n### 3.1 Intent Classification (Single LLM Call)\n\n9 intent types, classified + entities extracted in one call:\n\n| Intent | Example |\n|--------|---------|\n| `event_create` | \"Dinner at Mario's Friday 7pm\" |\n| `event_query` | \"What's happening this weekend?\" |\n| `event_rsvp_yes` | \"I'm in for the dinner\" |\n| `event_rsvp_no` | \"Can't make it\" |\n| `event_rsvp_maybe` | \"Maybe, I'll let you know\" |\n| `event_modify` | \"Move dinner to Saturday\" |\n| `event_cancel` | \"Cancel the hiking trip\" |\n| `event_remind` | \"Remind me about the concert 1 hour before\" |\n| `not_calendar` | \"lol nice photo\" (ignored) |\n\n### 3.2 LLM Prompt\n\n```python\nSYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a calendar assistant parsing messages from a group chat.\nGiven a message and recent chat context, respond with JSON only.\n\nSchema:\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\" | \"event_query\" | \"event_rsvp_yes\" | \"event_rsvp_no\" |\n            \"event_rsvp_maybe\" | \"event_modify\" | \"event_cancel\" | \"event_remind\" |\n            \"not_calendar\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.0-1.0,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"string or null\",\n    \"date_text\": \"string or null\",\n    \"location\": \"string or null\",\n    \"duration_minutes\": int or null,\n    \"participants\": [\"string\"] or [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"string or null\"\n  },\n  \"query\": {\n    \"time_range\": \"string or null\",\n    \"filter\": \"string or null\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"string\"]\n}\n\nRules:\n- \"I'm in\" with no prior event context = not_calendar\n- \"I'm in\" following an event proposal = event_rsvp_yes\n- Default duration is null (caller applies 2-hour default)\n- For RSVP/modify/cancel, reference_event = most recent matching event name\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Model:** `anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku` via OpenRouter\n**Cost:** ~$0.0003/message, ~$0.45/month at 50 messages/day\n**Latency:** ~400-800ms\n\n### 3.3 Date/Time Resolution\n\nUses `dateparser` with `PREFER_DATES_FROM: future` plus custom rules:\n\n| Input | Resolution |\n|-------|------------|\n| \"Friday\" | Next Friday, 7:00 PM (social default) |\n| \"Friday at 3\" | Next Friday, 3:00 PM |\n| \"this weekend\" | Saturday 10 AM - Sunday 6 PM |\n| \"tonight\" | Today 7:00 PM |\n| \"March 15 at 3\" | 2026-03-15T15:00:00 |\n| \"next week\" | **Ambiguous** -- ask for clarification |\n| \"2 hours before\" | event.start - 2h (for reminders) |\n\n**AM/PM heuristic:** Bare numbers 1-6 default to PM. Morning keywords (breakfast, brunch, hike, coffee) keep AM.\n\n### 3.4 Confirmation Flow\n\n| Condition | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| confidence >= 0.8, no ambiguities, no conflicts | Auto-confirm: create event, send summary |\n| confidence >= 0.8, has conflict | Warn + ask to proceed |\n| confidence 0.6-0.8 | Show interpretation, ask for yes/no |\n| confidence < 0.6 | Ask for clarification |\n| Pending confirmation expires | 10 minutes, auto-discard |\n\n**Auto-confirmed response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Got it!\n  Dinner at Mario's\n  Friday, March 13 at 7:00 PM\n  Location: Mario's\n  Duration: 2 hours\nReact with thumbs up to join, thumbs down to skip.\n```\n\n### 3.5 Pipeline Pseudocode\n\n```python\nasync def handle_signal_message(raw_msg):\n    text = raw_msg[\"message\"]\n    sender_phone = raw_msg[\"sender\"]\n    group_id = raw_msg[\"group_id\"]\n\n    # 1. Add to rolling context buffer (last 20 messages, 30 min window)\n    buffer.add(sender_phone, text, datetime.now())\n\n    # 2. Check pending confirmation\n    pending = pending_confirmations.get(sender_phone)\n    if pending and not pending.expired():\n        if is_affirmative(text): create_and_confirm(pending)\n        elif is_negative(text): discard(pending)\n        return\n\n    # 3. Classify + extract (single LLM call)\n    parsed = parse_message(text, sender_phone, buffer.recent(limit=5))\n    if parsed.intent == \"not_calendar\": return\n\n    # 4. Route by intent\n    match parsed.intent:\n        case \"event_create\":  handle_create(parsed, sender_phone, group_id)\n        case \"event_query\":   handle_query(parsed, group_id)\n        case \"event_rsvp_*\":  handle_rsvp(parsed, sender_phone, group_id)\n        case \"event_modify\":  handle_modify(parsed, sender_phone, group_id)\n        case \"event_cancel\":  handle_cancel(parsed, sender_phone, group_id)\n        case \"event_remind\":  handle_remind(parsed, sender_phone, group_id)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Query Patterns (Cypher)\n\n### Q1: \"What's coming up this week?\"\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event)\nWHERE e.status = \"active\"\n  AND e.start_datetime >= datetime()\n  AND e.start_datetime < datetime() + duration(\"P7D\")\nOPTIONAL MATCH (e)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(l:Location)\nOPTIONAL MATCH (p:Person)-[att:ATTENDING]->(e)\nWHERE att.rsvp = \"going\"\nWITH e, l, count(p) AS going_count\nRETURN e.name AS event, e.start_datetime AS starts,\n       l.name AS location, going_count\nORDER BY e.start_datetime ASC\n```\n\n### Q2: \"What events is Liz going to?\"\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (p:Person)-[att:ATTENDING]->(e:Event)\nWHERE toLower(p.name) = toLower($person_name)\n  AND att.rsvp IN [\"going\", \"maybe\"]\n  AND e.status = \"active\"\n  AND e.start_datetime >= datetime()\nOPTIONAL MATCH (e)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(l:Location)\nRETURN e.name AS event, e.start_datetime AS starts,\n       l.name AS location, att.rsvp AS rsvp\nORDER BY e.start_datetime ASC\n```\n\n### Q3: \"When is the next dinner?\" (Fulltext fuzzy search)\n\n```cypher\nCALL db.index.fulltext.queryNodes(\"event_search\", $search_term)\nYIELD node AS e, score\nWHERE e.status = \"active\" AND e.start_datetime >= datetime()\nWITH e, score ORDER BY e.start_datetime ASC LIMIT 1\nOPTIONAL MATCH (e)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(l:Location)\nOPTIONAL MATCH (p:Person)-[att:ATTENDING]->(e) WHERE att.rsvp = \"going\"\nWITH e, l, collect(p.name) AS attendees\nRETURN e.name, e.start_datetime, l.name AS location, attendees\n```\n\n### Q4: \"Who's going to [event]?\"\n\n```cypher\nCALL db.index.fulltext.queryNodes(\"event_search\", $event_query)\nYIELD node AS e, score\nWHERE e.status = \"active\"\nWITH e ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 1\nMATCH (p:Person)-[att:ATTENDING]->(e)\nRETURN e.name, p.name AS person, att.rsvp\nORDER BY att.rsvp ASC, p.name ASC\n```\n\n### Q5: \"Add me to [event]\" (RSVP)\n\n```cypher\nCALL db.index.fulltext.queryNodes(\"event_search\", $event_query)\nYIELD node AS e, score\nWHERE e.status = \"active\" AND e.start_datetime >= datetime()\nWITH e ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 1\nMATCH (p:Person {phone_number: $phone})\nMERGE (p)-[att:ATTENDING]->(e)\nON CREATE SET att.rsvp = \"going\", att.rsvp_at = datetime(), att.added_by = \"self\"\nON MATCH SET att.rsvp = \"going\", att.rsvp_at = datetime()\nRETURN e.name AS event, p.name AS person\n```\n\n### Q6: \"Cancel [event]\" (Creator-only soft delete)\n\n```cypher\nCALL db.index.fulltext.queryNodes(\"event_search\", $event_query)\nYIELD node AS e, score\nWHERE e.status = \"active\"\nWITH e ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 1\nMATCH (e)-[:CREATED_BY]->(creator:Person {phone_number: $phone})\nSET e.status = \"cancelled\", e.updated_at = datetime()\nRETURN e.name AS event, \"cancelled\" AS status\n```\n\n### Q7: \"Remind me about [event] 1 hour before\"\n\n```cypher\nCALL db.index.fulltext.queryNodes(\"event_search\", $event_query)\nYIELD node AS e, score\nWHERE e.status = \"active\" AND e.start_datetime >= datetime()\nWITH e ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 1\nMATCH (p:Person {phone_number: $phone})\nWITH e, p, e.start_datetime - duration($offset) AS remind_time\nCREATE (r:Reminder {\n    reminder_id: randomUUID(),\n    remind_at: remind_time,\n    offset_desc: $offset_desc,\n    sent: false,\n    channel: \"signal\",\n    created_at: datetime()\n})\nCREATE (r)-[:REMINDER_FOR]->(e)\nCREATE (r)-[:REMIND]->(p)\nRETURN e.name, r.remind_at, p.name\n```\n\n### Q8: Full event creation\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (creator:Person {phone_number: $creator_phone})\nCREATE (e:Event {\n    event_id: $event_id,\n    name: $name,\n    description: $description,\n    start_datetime: datetime($start),\n    end_datetime: CASE WHEN $end IS NOT NULL THEN datetime($end) ELSE null END,\n    all_day: $all_day,\n    status: \"active\",\n    visibility: \"group\",\n    source_message: $source_message,\n    created_at: datetime(),\n    updated_at: datetime()\n})\nCREATE (e)-[:CREATED_BY]->(creator)\nCREATE (creator)-[:ATTENDING {rsvp: \"going\", rsvp_at: datetime(), added_by: \"self\"}]->(e)\nWITH e\nFOREACH (_ IN CASE WHEN $location_key IS NOT NULL THEN [1] ELSE [] END |\n    MERGE (l:Location {name_key: $location_key})\n    ON CREATE SET l.name = $location_name, l.created_at = datetime()\n    CREATE (e)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(l)\n)\nRETURN e.event_id, e.name, e.start_datetime\n```\n\n### Q9: Reminder cron (find due reminders)\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (r:Reminder)-[:REMINDER_FOR]->(e:Event),\n      (r)-[:REMIND]->(p:Person)\nWHERE r.sent = false\n  AND r.remind_at <= datetime()\n  AND e.status = \"active\"\nRETURN r.reminder_id, e.name, e.start_datetime, p.name, p.phone_number, r.channel\nORDER BY r.remind_at ASC\n```\n\n### Q10: Daily digest (next 3 days)\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event)\nWHERE e.status = \"active\"\n  AND e.start_datetime >= datetime()\n  AND e.start_datetime < datetime() + duration(\"P3D\")\nOPTIONAL MATCH (e)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(l:Location)\nOPTIONAL MATCH (p:Person)-[att:ATTENDING]->(e) WHERE att.rsvp = \"going\"\nWITH e, l, collect(p.name) AS attendees\nRETURN e.name, e.start_datetime, l.name AS location, attendees\nORDER BY e.start_datetime ASC LIMIT 10\n```\n\n### Q11: Conflict detection\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event)\nWHERE e.status = \"active\"\n  AND e.start_datetime < datetime($proposed_end)\n  AND e.end_datetime > datetime($proposed_start)\nRETURN e.name, e.start_datetime, e.end_datetime\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Reminder System\n\n### Cron Job: `calendar_reminder_worker.py`\n\nRuns every minute via launchd (`com.kurultai.calendar-reminders`).\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Check Neo4j for due reminders, send via signal-cli.\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom neo4j_task_tracker import get_driver\n\nSIGNAL_ACCOUNT = \"+15165643945\"\nGROUP_ID = \"BROemHVncLgSz8tReUKBz6V3BeDhDB0EXaJd+sRp6oA=\"\n\ndef check_and_send_reminders():\n    driver = get_driver()\n    with driver.session() as session:\n        # Find due unsent reminders\n        result = session.run(\"\"\"\n            MATCH (r:Reminder)-[:REMINDER_FOR]->(e:Event),\n                  (r)-[:REMIND]->(p:Person)\n            WHERE r.sent = false AND r.remind_at <= datetime() AND e.status = \"active\"\n            RETURN r.reminder_id AS rid, e.name AS event,\n                   e.start_datetime AS starts, p.phone_number AS phone, p.name AS name\n        \"\"\")\n        for record in result:\n            msg = f\"Reminder: {record['event']} at {record['starts'].strftime('%I:%M %p')}\"\n            send_signal_dm(record['phone'], msg)\n            # Mark sent\n            session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (r:Reminder {reminder_id: $rid})\n                SET r.sent = true, r.sent_at = datetime()\n            \"\"\", rid=record['rid'])\n    driver.close()\n\ndef send_signal_dm(phone, message):\n    subprocess.run([\n        \"signal-cli\", \"-a\", SIGNAL_ACCOUNT,\n        \"send\", \"-m\", message, phone\n    ], capture_output=True, timeout=10)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    check_and_send_reminders()\n```\n\n### Default Reminders\n\n- Auto-create a \"1 hour before\" reminder for the event creator on every new event\n- Users can add custom reminders (\"remind me 2 hours before\")\n- Max 3 reminders per person per event (rate limit)\n\n### Morning Digest (Optional)\n\nDaily at 8 AM, send the group a summary of today + tomorrow's events using Q10.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Access Control\n\n### Roles\n\n| Role | Who | Capabilities |\n|------|-----|-------------|\n| **admin** | Danny | Create, query, RSVP, modify any, cancel any, manage members |\n| **member** | Liz, others in group | Create, query, RSVP, modify own, cancel own, set reminders |\n| **system** | Calendar bot | Send reminders, auto-cleanup, daily digest |\n\n### Authorization Rules\n\n- **Cancel:** Only creator can cancel (Cypher enforces via CREATED_BY match)\n- **Modify:** Only creator can modify (same pattern)\n- **Admin override:** Danny (admin) can cancel/modify anyone's events\n- **New group members:** Auto-trust anyone who sends from the authorized Signal group\n- **Left members:** Soft-disable (events preserved, pending reminders cancelled)\n\n### Identity\n\n- **Primary key:** Phone number (E.164)\n- **Secondary:** Signal UUID (stored when available, future-proofing)\n- **Display:** First name from Person node\n\n### Input Validation\n\n- All Cypher uses parameterized queries (already standard in existing codebase)\n- Event names: max 200 chars, stripped of control characters\n- Descriptions: max 1000 chars\n- LLM output treated as untrusted -- validated through same Pydantic pipeline\n- Rate limits: 5 event creates/hour, 30 queries/hour per person\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Schema + Core CRUD (1 session)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 1.1 | Run schema creation Cypher (constraints, indexes, fulltext) |\n| 1.2 | Seed Person nodes for Danny, Liz |\n| 1.3 | Create `neo4j_calendar.py` — CRUD functions using get_driver() |\n| 1.4 | Test: create event, query event, RSVP, cancel |\n\n**Files:**\n- `~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/neo4j_calendar.py` (new)\n- Schema Cypher applied directly to Neo4j\n\n### Phase 2: NLP Pipeline (1 session)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 2.1 | `pip3 install dateparser python-dateutil pytz` |\n| 2.2 | Create `calendar_parser.py` — LLM classification + dateparser resolution |\n| 2.3 | Create Pydantic models (ParsedMessage, ResolvedEvent, etc.) |\n| 2.4 | Test with 12 example messages (unit tests for dateparser, integration for LLM) |\n\n**Files:**\n- `~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/calendar_parser.py` (new)\n\n### Phase 3: Signal Integration (1 session)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 3.1 | Create `calendar_handler.py` — message intake, routing, response formatting |\n| 3.2 | Hook into existing Signal message processing pipeline |\n| 3.3 | Rolling context buffer (last 20 messages per group, 30 min window) |\n| 3.4 | Pending confirmation state machine (10 min timeout) |\n| 3.5 | Test end-to-end: Signal message -> parsed event -> Neo4j -> confirmation |\n\n**Files:**\n- `~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/calendar_handler.py` (new)\n\n### Phase 4: Reminder System (1 session)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 4.1 | Create `calendar_reminder_worker.py` |\n| 4.2 | Create launchd plist `com.kurultai.calendar-reminders` (runs every minute) |\n| 4.3 | Auto-create 1-hour-before reminder on event creation |\n| 4.4 | Optional: morning digest cron (daily at 8 AM) |\n| 4.5 | Test: create event with reminder, verify delivery |\n\n**Files:**\n- `~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/calendar_reminder_worker.py` (new)\n- `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.calendar-reminders.plist` (new)\n\n### Phase 5: Polish + Hardening (1 session)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 5.1 | Rate limiting (in-memory sliding window per user) |\n| 5.2 | Input sanitization (max lengths, control char stripping) |\n| 5.3 | Audit logging (calendar operations to PipelineEvent nodes) |\n| 5.4 | Data retention: auto-prune events older than 90 days |\n| 5.5 | Error handling: Neo4j down -> filesystem fallback, LLM down -> queue |\n\n### Dependencies to Install\n\n```bash\npip3 install dateparser python-dateutil pytz\n```\n\nEverything else (neo4j driver, openai client, pydantic, signal-cli) is already available.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Detailed Reports\n\nThe following specialist reports contain additional depth:\n\n| Report | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| Neo4j Schema (full Cypher) | `workspace/signal-calendar-neo4j-schema.cypher` |\n| NLP Pipeline Design | `workspace/signal-calendar-nlp-pipeline-design.md` |\n| Security Model | `workspace/signal-calendar-security-model.md` |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| LLM misclassifies message | Medium | Confirmation flow for confidence < 0.8 |\n| OpenRouter API down | Medium | Queue messages, process when API returns (5s timeout) |\n| Neo4j down | Medium | Filesystem fallback (same pattern as existing task tracker) |\n| Duplicate event creation | Low | Hash name + start_datetime + group_id, check before insert |\n| Prompt injection via event names | Low | Parameterized Cypher, LLM output treated as untrusted |\n| Phone number change | Low | Signal UUID stored as secondary identity |\n| Timezone confusion | Low | All stored as UTC, displayed in America/New_York |\n| Spam event creation | Low | Rate limit: 5 creates/hour per person |\n\n---\n\n## 10. Example Interactions\n\n**Create:**\n```\n[Liz]: Dinner at Mario's Friday at 7pm\n[Calendar]: Got it! Dinner at Mario's - Friday, March 13 at 7:00 PM\n  Location: Mario's | Duration: 2 hours\n  React thumbs up to join, thumbs down to skip.\n```\n\n**RSVP:**\n```\n[Danny]: I'm in\n[Calendar]: You're in for Dinner at Mario's (Fri 7 PM)\n  Attending: Liz, Danny\n```\n\n**Query:**\n```\n[Danny]: What's happening this weekend?\n[Calendar]: This weekend:\n  Fri 7:00 PM - Dinner at Mario's (Liz, Danny)\n  Sat 9:00 AM - Hike (Liz)\n  Nothing on Sunday yet!\n```\n\n**Remind:**\n```\n[Danny]: Remind me about dinner 1 hour before\n[Calendar]: Reminder set: Dinner at Mario's\n  I'll ping you Friday at 6:00 PM\n```\n\n**Cancel:**\n```\n[Liz]: Cancel the hike, weather's bad\n[Calendar]: Cancelled: Hike (Sat 9 AM)\n  Reason: weather's bad\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. Itinerary Support (Extension)\n\nAn **itinerary** is a collection of related events grouped together (e.g., a trip, conference, or multi-day plan). Events can belong to multiple itineraries.\n\n### 11.1 Neo4j Schema Additions\n\nSee `workspace/signal-calendar-itinerary-schema-extension.cypher` for full schema.\n\n#### New Node Type: Itinerary\n\n| Label | Primary Key | Properties |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| **Itinerary** | `itinerary_id` | name, name_key (normalized), description, owner_phone, start_date (computed), end_date (computed), event_count (computed), is_active, visibility, cover_image, created_at, updated_at |\n\n#### New Relationship: PART_OF_ITINERARY\n\n```\n(Event)-[:PART_OF_ITINERARY {added_at, added_by, position_hint}]->(Itinerary)\n```\n\nEvents can have multiple PART_OF_ITINERARY relationships (same event in multiple itineraries).\n\n#### Updated Graph Topology\n\n```\n                +---------+\n                |  Agent  |\n                +----^----+\n                     | OPERATES_AS\n                +----+----+\n    +-----------| Person  |----------------+\n    |           +----+----+                |\n    |                |                     | CREATED_BY\n    |                |                     v\n    |          +-----v-----+         +------------+\n    |          |           |         |            |\n    |          |   Event   |         | Itinerary  |\n    |          |           |         |            |\n    |          +-----+-----+         +------------+\n    |                | PART_OF_ITINERARY\n    +----------------+\n      (REMIND, etc.)\n```\n\n### 11.2 New Intent Types\n\n| Intent | Example |\n|--------|---------|\n| `itinerary_create` | \"create an itinerary for NYC next weekend\" |\n| `itinerary_add` | \"add dinner to the NYC trip\" |\n| `itinerary_remove` | \"remove the museum from NYC trip\" |\n| `itinerary_query` | \"show me the NYC trip\", \"what's the plan?\" |\n| `itinerary_share` | \"share the NYC trip\" |\n| `itinerary_modify` | \"rename the trip to Spring Fling\" |\n\n### 11.3 LLM Prompt Extension\n\nExtend the JSON schema with:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"itinerary\": {\n    \"name\": \"string or null\",\n    \"reference_itinerary\": \"string or null\",\n    \"reference_event\": \"string or null\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 11.4 Key Query Patterns\n\n#### Create Itinerary\n```cypher\nMATCH (owner:Person {phone_number: $owner_phone})\nCREATE (i:Itinerary {\n    itinerary_id: \"itn-\" + randomUUID(),\n    name: $name,\n    name_key: toLower($name) + \":\" + $owner_phone,\n    description: $description,\n    owner_phone: $owner_phone,\n    start_date: null,\n    end_date: null,\n    event_count: 0,\n    is_active: true,\n    visibility: \"group\",\n    created_at: datetime(),\n    updated_at: datetime()\n})\nCREATE (i)-[:CREATED_BY]->(owner)\nRETURN i.itinerary_id, i.name;\n```\n\n#### Add Event to Itinerary\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event {event_id: $event_id})\nMATCH (i:Itinerary {name_key: $itinerary_name_key})\nCREATE (e)-[:PART_OF_ITINERARY {\n    added_at: datetime(),\n    added_by: $adder_phone,\n    position_hint: 0\n}]->(i)\n// Then update computed properties: event_count, start_date, end_date\n```\n\n#### Show Full Itinerary (Chronological)\n```cypher\nMATCH (i:Itinerary {name_key: $itinerary_name_key})\nMATCH (i)<-[:PART_OF_ITINERARY]-(e:Event)\nWHERE e.status = \"active\" OR e.status IS NULL\nOPTIONAL MATCH (e)-[:AT_LOCATION]->(l:Location)\nWITH i, e, l ORDER BY e.start_datetime ASC\nRETURN i.name, collect({\n    event: e.name,\n    start: e.start_datetime,\n    location: l.name,\n    duration: e.end_datetime - e.start_datetime\n}) AS events;\n```\n\n#### List User's Itineraries\n```cypher\nMATCH (i:Itinerary {owner_phone: $owner_phone})\nWHERE i.is_active = true\nRETURN i.name, i.start_date, i.end_date, i.event_count\nORDER BY i.start_date ASC;\n```\n\n### 11.5 Computed Properties\n\nThe Itinerary node maintains these computed properties that MUST be updated when events are added/removed/modified:\n\n| Property | Computed From |\n|----------|---------------|\n| `start_date` | MIN(Event.start_datetime) for all linked events |\n| `end_date` | MAX(Event.end_datetime) for all linked events |\n| `event_count` | COUNT of PART_OF_ITINERARY relationships |\n| `is_active` | event_count > 0 AND at least one event is future |\n\n### 11.6 Message Templates\n\nSee `workspace/signal-calendar-itinerary-message-templates.md` for full template designs:\n\n| Template | Use Case | Character Count |\n|----------|----------|-----------------|\n| Itinerary Created | New itinerary | ~140 |\n| Event Added | Link event to itinerary | ~150 |\n| Event Removed | Unlink event from itinerary | ~85 |\n| Full Display | \"Show me the trip\" | ~820-1800 |\n| Compact Summary | \"How many events?\" | ~155 |\n| Shared | \"Share the itinerary\" | ~870 |\n| Error Cases | Not found, already in, etc. | ~75-250 |\n\n### 11.7 Example Interactions\n\n#### Creating an Itinerary\n```\n[Danny]: create an itinerary called NYC Weekend Trip\n[Calendar] Itinerary created!\n  NYC Weekend Trip\n  Created by Danny\n  No events yet\n\nTo add events, say:\n  \"add [event] to NYC trip\"\n```\n\n#### Adding Events\n```\n[Danny]: Dinner at L'Artusi Friday at 8pm\n[Calendar] Got it!\n  Dinner at L'Artusi\n  Friday, March 14 at 8:00 PM\n  ...\n\n[Danny]: add that to NYC trip\n[Calendar] Added to NYC Weekend Trip:\n  Dinner at L'Artusi\n  Friday, Mar 14 at 8:00 PM\n  (1 event total)\n```\n\n#### Querying\n```\n[Liz]: what's the plan for NYC?\n[Calendar] NYC Weekend Trip\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n3-day trip  •  Mar 14-16  •  7 events\n\n── Friday, March 14 ──────────\n\n  6:00 PM  Check in at The Wythe Hotel\n           Duration: 1 hr\n           │\n           ╵ 1 hr gap\n           │\n  8:00 PM  Dinner at L'Artusi\n           Duration: 2 hrs\n\n[... rest of itinerary ...]\n```\n\n#### Sharing\n```\n[Danny]: share the NYC trip\n[Calendar] Danny shared an itinerary:\n\nNYC Weekend Trip\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n[... full itinerary ...]\n\n─────────────────────────────\nGoing: Danny, Liz\n\nReply \"I'm in for NYC trip\" to join all\nor RSVP to individual events by name.\n```\n\n#### Joining via Share\n```\n[Alex]: I'm in for NYC trip\n[Calendar] You're in for NYC Weekend Trip!\n  Added to all 7 events (Mar 14-16)\n  Going to all: Danny, Liz, you\n```\n\n### 11.8 Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Name Key Uniqueness:** The `name_key` format is `lowercase(name):owner_phone`. This ensures uniqueness per owner while allowing different owners to have itineraries with the same display name.\n\n2. **Chronological Ordering:** Events are ALWAYS ordered by `start_datetime ASC`. The `position_hint` relationship property is reserved for future manual reordering.\n\n3. **Multi-Itineraries:** An event can belong to multiple itineraries. The application should handle this gracefully.\n\n4. **Deletion Behavior:**\n   - Deleting an itinerary does NOT delete its events\n   - Deleting an event removes its PART_OF_ITINERARY relationships automatically\n\n5. **Implementation Order:** Build core event system first (Phases 1-5), then add itineraries as Phase 6.\n\n### 11.9 Additional Files\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `signal-calendar-itinerary-schema-extension.cypher` | Full Cypher schema for itineraries |\n| `signal-calendar-itinerary-message-templates.md` | UX templates for itinerary messages |\n\n---\n\n## 12. Implementation Plan Update\n\n### Phase 6: Itinerary Support (1-2 sessions)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 6.1 | Run itinerary schema extension (constraints, indexes) |\n| 6.2 | Extend `calendar_parser.py` with itinerary intent types |\n| 6.3 | Create `itinerary_handler.py` — itinerary CRUD operations |\n| 6.4 | Create `itinerary_formatter.py` — message template rendering |\n| 6.5 | Test end-to-end: create itinerary, add events, query, share |\n| 6.6 | Add computed property triggers (auto-update start/end dates) |\n\n**Files:**\n- `~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/itinerary_handler.py` (new)\n- `~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/itinerary_formatter.py` (new)\n- Schema extension Cypher applied to Neo4j\n\n---\n\n## 12. People Attachment Support (Extension)\n\nThis section extends the calendar system to support attaching people to events with proper permissions, notifications, and RSVP tracking.\n\n### 12.1 Features\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Signal Commands** | \"add Liz to dinner\", \"invite Alex to hike\", \"+@Liz\" |\n| **Permission Model** | Creator can add anyone; members can only self-RSVP; admin override |\n| **RSVP Tracking** | going/maybe/declined with full audit trail |\n| **Notifications** | Person notified when added; attendees notified of changes |\n| **Query Patterns** | \"who's coming?\", \"what is Liz going to?\", \"is Alex going?\" |\n\n### 12.2 Schema Additions\n\n**New Node:** `EventNotification`\n- Tracks pending notifications for people additions, RSVP changes, event modifications\n- Properties: notification_id, type, event_id, recipient_phone, message, sent, sent_at\n\n**Extended Relationships:**\n- `(Person)-[:ATTENDING {rsvp, rsvp_at, added_by, added_at, notified}]->(Event)`\n\n### 12.3 Key Query Patterns\n\n| Query | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| Q20 | Add person to event (with permission check) |\n| Q21 | Remove person from event (with permission check) |\n| Q22 | Get all attendees with RSVP breakdown |\n| Q23 | Get all events for a person |\n| Q24 | Check specific person's RSVP for event |\n| Q26 | Create notification when person added |\n| Q27 | Get pending notifications to send |\n\n### 12.4 Implementation (Phase 7)\n\n| Task | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 7.1 | Extend calendar_parser.py with person intents |\n| 7.2 | Create attendance_permissions.py |\n| 7.3 | Extend neo4j_calendar.py with person queries |\n| 7.4 | Create event_notifications.py |\n| 7.5 | Update calendar_handler.py with person flows |\n| 7.6 | Add message templates |\n\n### 12.5 Documentation\n\n| Document | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| Full Design | `jochi/workspace/signal-calendar-people-attachment-design.md` |\n| Schema Cypher | `jochi/workspace/signal-calendar-people-attachment-schema.cypher` |\n| Summary | `jochi/workspace/signal-calendar-people-attachment-summary.md` |\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772866306653}}
{"type":"message","id":"64f817c7","parentId":"afc80896","timestamp":"2026-03-07T06:51:46.710Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6508046e4b974e98875665f7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Signal Group Calendar -- NLP Parsing Pipeline Design\n\n**Author:** Temujin (Developer)\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\n**System:** Kurultai Signal Calendar\n\n---\n\n## 0. Environment Inventory\n\n| Component | Detail |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Runtime | Python 3.14.3 on Mac Mini (Darwin 25.3.0) |\n| Signal | signal-cli 0.13.24 (`/opt/homebrew/bin/signal-cli`) |\n| Graph DB | Neo4j (bolt://localhost:7687, neo4j driver 6.1.0) |\n| LLM | OpenRouter API (key in `~/.openclaw/config/.env`) |\n| Validation | Pydantic 2.12.5 |\n| HTTP | httpx 0.28.1, openai 2.24.0 (OpenAI-compatible client for OpenRouter) |\n| Date parsing | **Not installed** -- dateparser/python-dateutil need to be added |\n| Timezone | US/Pacific assumed (Mac Mini location) |\n\n### Missing dependencies to install\n\n```bash\npip3 install dateparser python-dateutil pytz\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n```\nSignal Group Chat\n       |\n       v\n  signal-cli (JSON-RPC or dbus)\n       |\n       v\n  message_intake.py          # Receives raw messages\n       |\n       v\n  classifier.py              # Intent classification (LLM)\n       |\n       v\n  entity_extractor.py        # Structured extraction (LLM + dateparser)\n       |\n       v\n  resolver.py                # Date/time resolution, conflict check\n       |\n       v\n  confirmation.py            # Build confirmation message, send back via signal-cli\n       |\n       v\n  neo4j_calendar.py          # Write Event nodes to Neo4j\n```\n\nEach stage is a pure function that takes input and returns a typed Pydantic model. The pipeline is synchronous per-message (latency budget: <3 seconds total including LLM call).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Message Classification\n\n### Recommendation: Single LLM call with structured output\n\nClassification and entity extraction should happen in **one LLM call**, not two. Splitting them doubles latency and cost for no benefit -- the LLM needs to understand the message meaning for classification anyway, so it should extract entities at the same time.\n\n### Intent Taxonomy\n\n| Intent | Description | Examples |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `event_create` | User wants to create a new event | \"Dinner at Mario's Friday 7pm\" |\n| `event_query` | User wants to know what's scheduled | \"What's happening this weekend?\" |\n| `event_rsvp_yes` | User confirms attendance | \"I'm in\", \"Count me in for dinner\" |\n| `event_rsvp_no` | User declines attendance | \"Can't make it\", \"I'm out\" |\n| `event_rsvp_maybe` | User is uncertain | \"Maybe, I'll let you know\" |\n| `event_modify` | User wants to change an existing event | \"Move dinner to Saturday\" |\n| `event_cancel` | User wants to cancel an event | \"Cancel the hiking trip\" |\n| `event_remind` | User wants a reminder set | \"Remind me about the concert tomorrow\" |\n| `not_calendar` | Message is not calendar-related | \"lol\", \"nice photo\", \"who's bringing beer?\" |\n\n### LLM Prompt for Combined Classification + Extraction\n\n```python\nSYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a calendar assistant parsing messages from a group chat.\n\nGiven a message and recent chat context, respond with JSON only. No explanation.\n\nSchema:\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\" | \"event_query\" | \"event_rsvp_yes\" | \"event_rsvp_no\" |\n            \"event_rsvp_maybe\" | \"event_modify\" | \"event_cancel\" | \"event_remind\" |\n            \"not_calendar\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.0-1.0,\n  \"event\": {                          // null if not_calendar\n    \"name\": \"string or null\",\n    \"date_text\": \"string or null\",    // raw date/time text as written\n    \"location\": \"string or null\",\n    \"duration_minutes\": int or null,\n    \"participants\": [\"string\"] or [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"string or null\"  // for modify/cancel/rsvp: which event\n  },\n  \"query\": {                          // only for event_query\n    \"time_range\": \"string or null\",\n    \"filter\": \"string or null\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"string\"]           // anything unclear\n}\n\nRules:\n- \"I'm in\" / \"count me in\" with no context = not_calendar (need reference event)\n- \"I'm in\" following an event creation = event_rsvp_yes referencing that event\n- If the message contains multiple events, return the primary one and note others in ambiguities\n- confidence < 0.6 = flag for confirmation\n- Default duration is null (caller will apply 2-hour default)\n- Participants are first names only as mentioned in the message\n- For RSVP/modify/cancel, reference_event should match the most recent relevant event name\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Why LLM-only for classification (not regex/keyword)\n\nFriend-group messages are wildly informal:\n- \"mario's fri 7\" (no verb, no preposition)\n- \"let's do the thing saturday\" (no event name beyond \"the thing\")\n- \"hiking?? this weekend anyone?\" (question mark doesn't mean query -- it means proposal)\n- \"nah\" (RSVP no, but only with context)\n\nRegex-based classifiers would need hundreds of patterns and still miss edge cases. A single LLM call with structured output handles all of these naturally. At ~200 input tokens + ~150 output tokens per message, cost is roughly $0.001 per message with Claude Haiku or Gemini Flash via OpenRouter.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Entity Extraction\n\nEntity extraction happens inside the same LLM call (Section 2). The LLM returns `date_text` as the raw string the user wrote. A second stage then resolves this into absolute datetimes.\n\n### Pydantic Models\n\n```python\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n\nclass Intent(str, Enum):\n    EVENT_CREATE = \"event_create\"\n    EVENT_QUERY = \"event_query\"\n    RSVP_YES = \"event_rsvp_yes\"\n    RSVP_NO = \"event_rsvp_no\"\n    RSVP_MAYBE = \"event_rsvp_maybe\"\n    EVENT_MODIFY = \"event_modify\"\n    EVENT_CANCEL = \"event_cancel\"\n    EVENT_REMIND = \"event_remind\"\n    NOT_CALENDAR = \"not_calendar\"\n\n\nclass EventExtraction(BaseModel):\n    name: Optional[str] = None\n    date_text: Optional[str] = None\n    location: Optional[str] = None\n    duration_minutes: Optional[int] = None\n    participants: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    reference_event: Optional[str] = None\n\n\nclass QueryExtraction(BaseModel):\n    time_range: Optional[str] = None\n    filter: Optional[str] = None\n\n\nclass ParsedMessage(BaseModel):\n    intent: Intent\n    confidence: float = Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    event: Optional[EventExtraction] = None\n    query: Optional[QueryExtraction] = None\n    ambiguities: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    sender: str = \"\"\n    raw_message: str = \"\"\n    timestamp: datetime = Field(default_factory=datetime.now)\n\n\nclass ResolvedEvent(BaseModel):\n    name: str\n    start_datetime: datetime\n    end_datetime: datetime\n    location: Optional[str] = None\n    participants: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    reminders: list[datetime] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    created_by: str = \"\"\n    source_message: str = \"\"\n    confidence: float = 1.0\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Date/Time Resolution\n\n### Strategy: dateparser first, LLM fallback for truly ambiguous cases\n\nAfter the LLM extracts `date_text` (e.g., \"next Friday at 7pm\"), we resolve it to an absolute datetime. This is a **hybrid approach** but weighted heavily toward the deterministic library path.\n\n### Resolution Pipeline\n\n```python\nimport dateparser\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom zoneinfo import ZoneInfo\n\nLOCAL_TZ = ZoneInfo(\"America/Los_Angeles\")\nDEFAULT_DURATION = timedelta(hours=2)\n\n\ndef resolve_datetime(date_text: str, reference_time: datetime = None) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns:\n      {\n        \"start\": datetime,\n        \"end\": datetime | None,\n        \"is_ambiguous\": bool,\n        \"interpretation\": str,    # human-readable explanation\n        \"alternatives\": [datetime] # if ambiguous, other possible interpretations\n      }\n    \"\"\"\n    if reference_time is None:\n        reference_time = datetime.now(LOCAL_TZ)\n\n    # --- Special patterns handled before dateparser ---\n\n    # \"this weekend\" -> Saturday 10:00 AM to Sunday 6:00 PM\n    if _is_weekend_reference(date_text):\n        sat = _next_weekday(reference_time, 5)  # Saturday\n        return {\n            \"start\": sat.replace(hour=10, minute=0),\n            \"end\": (sat + timedelta(days=1)).replace(hour=18, minute=0),\n            \"is_ambiguous\": False,\n            \"interpretation\": f\"This weekend: {sat.strftime('%b %d')} - {(sat + timedelta(days=1)).strftime('%b %d')}\",\n            \"alternatives\": []\n        }\n\n    # \"tonight\" -> today at 7:00 PM\n    if date_text.strip().lower() == \"tonight\":\n        tonight = reference_time.replace(hour=19, minute=0, second=0)\n        return {\n            \"start\": tonight,\n            \"end\": tonight + DEFAULT_DURATION,\n            \"is_ambiguous\": False,\n            \"interpretation\": f\"Tonight at 7:00 PM\",\n            \"alternatives\": []\n        }\n\n    # --- dateparser for everything else ---\n    settings = {\n        'PREFER_DATES_FROM': 'future',\n        'PREFER_DAY_OF_MONTH': 'first',\n        'RELATIVE_BASE': reference_time.replace(tzinfo=None),\n        'RETURN_AS_TIMEZONE_AWARE': False,\n        'TIMEZONE': 'America/Los_Angeles',\n    }\n\n    parsed = dateparser.parse(date_text, settings=settings)\n\n    if parsed is None:\n        return {\n            \"start\": None,\n            \"end\": None,\n            \"is_ambiguous\": True,\n            \"interpretation\": f\"Could not parse: '{date_text}'\",\n            \"alternatives\": []\n        }\n\n    # Localize the result\n    start = parsed.replace(tzinfo=LOCAL_TZ)\n\n    # Detect ambiguity: bare day names, \"next week\", etc.\n    ambiguous = _detect_ambiguity(date_text, start, reference_time)\n\n    return {\n        \"start\": start,\n        \"end\": start + DEFAULT_DURATION,\n        \"is_ambiguous\": ambiguous,\n        \"interpretation\": f\"{start.strftime('%A, %B %d at %I:%M %p %Z')}\",\n        \"alternatives\": _generate_alternatives(date_text, start) if ambiguous else []\n    }\n```\n\n### Specific Resolution Rules\n\n| Input | Resolution | Notes |\n|-------|------------|-------|\n| `\"Friday\"` | Next Friday, 7:00 PM | `PREFER_DATES_FROM: future`. Default to evening for social events. |\n| `\"Friday at 3\"` | Next Friday, 3:00 PM | Bare number < 12 and social context = PM. |\n| `\"this weekend\"` | Saturday 10 AM - Sunday 6 PM | Special-cased. Creates a range, not a point. |\n| `\"7pm\"` | Today at 7 PM if > now, else tomorrow 7 PM | dateparser handles this with `PREFER_DATES_FROM: future`. |\n| `\"March 15 at 3\"` | 2026-03-15T15:00:00 | Absolute date, bare \"3\" = 3 PM (social context heuristic). |\n| `\"tomorrow morning\"` | Tomorrow at 10:00 AM | \"Morning\" = 10 AM for social events. |\n| `\"next week\"` | **Ambiguous** -- flag for confirmation | Could mean Monday, could mean any day. Ask the user. |\n| `\"in 2 hours\"` | reference_time + 2h | Relative, unambiguous. |\n| `\"the 15th\"` | 15th of current month (or next month if past) | dateparser `PREFER_DATES_FROM: future` handles this. |\n| `\"NYE\"` | December 31 at 9:00 PM | Special-cased holiday. |\n\n### AM/PM Heuristic for Social Events\n\nWhen time is given as a bare number (e.g., \"at 3\", \"at 7\"), apply social context:\n- 1-6 without AM/PM -> PM (nobody schedules group dinner at 3 AM)\n- 7-11 without AM/PM -> context-dependent: \"breakfast at 8\" = AM, \"drinks at 8\" = PM\n- 12 -> noon unless \"midnight\" is mentioned\n- The LLM extraction helps here: the `name` field (\"dinner\", \"brunch\", \"hike\") disambiguates\n\n```python\ndef apply_ampm_heuristic(hour: int, event_name: str = \"\") -> int:\n    \"\"\"For bare hour numbers, infer AM/PM from event context.\"\"\"\n    morning_events = {\"breakfast\", \"brunch\", \"coffee\", \"run\", \"hike\", \"yoga\", \"morning\"}\n    name_lower = (event_name or \"\").lower()\n\n    if any(kw in name_lower for kw in morning_events):\n        return hour  # Keep as AM\n\n    # Social default: bare hours 1-6 are PM\n    if 1 <= hour <= 6:\n        return hour + 12\n\n    # 7-11: default PM for social, unless morning keyword\n    if 7 <= hour <= 11:\n        return hour + 12  # Default PM for social events\n\n    return hour\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Implementation Approach Recommendation\n\n### Verdict: Option A (LLM-based) with dateparser validation\n\n**Use the LLM for classification + entity extraction. Use dateparser for datetime resolution and validation.**\n\nHere is the reasoning:\n\n#### Why not pure hybrid (Option B)?\n\nThe hybrid approach (regex patterns + dateparser + LLM fallback) sounds efficient but creates a maintenance nightmare for this use case:\n\n1. **Friend-group messages are not formal.** \"mario's fri 7\" has no verb, no preposition, no punctuation. Regex classifiers need \"create event\", \"schedule\", \"let's do\" patterns. Real humans write none of these.\n\n2. **Context dependence.** \"I'm in\" is an RSVP only if a recent message proposed an event. \"Saturday?\" is a proposal, not a query. You need semantic understanding, not pattern matching.\n\n3. **Regex maintenance cost.** Every new message pattern someone uses (\"who's down for...\", \"we should...\", \"anyone free...\") requires a new regex. The LLM handles all of these out of the box.\n\n#### Why not pure LLM (no dateparser)?\n\nLLMs are unreliable at date arithmetic. \"Next Friday\" when today is Wednesday -- is that in 2 days or 9 days? LLMs sometimes get this wrong. `dateparser` with `PREFER_DATES_FROM: future` is deterministic and correct.\n\n#### The recommended split\n\n| Stage | Tool | Why |\n|-------|------|-----|\n| Classification | LLM (Claude Haiku / Gemini Flash) | Semantic understanding of informal text |\n| Entity extraction | LLM (same call) | Structured output from unstructured text |\n| Date/time resolution | dateparser + custom rules | Deterministic, testable, no hallucination |\n| Conflict detection | Neo4j Cypher query | Graph DB does this natively |\n| Confirmation text | Template (Python f-string) | No need for LLM here |\n\n#### Cost estimate\n\n- Model: `anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku` via OpenRouter\n- Input: ~250 tokens (system prompt + message + context)\n- Output: ~100 tokens (JSON)\n- Cost: ~$0.0003 per message\n- At 50 messages/day: ~$0.015/day, ~$0.45/month\n- Latency: ~400-800ms for Haiku via OpenRouter\n\n---\n\n## 6. LLM Integration Code\n\n```python\nimport json\nimport httpx\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\nOPENROUTER_API_KEY = \"...\"  # from ~/.openclaw/config/.env\nMODEL = \"anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku\"  # fast, cheap, good at structured output\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=\"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\",\n    api_key=OPENROUTER_API_KEY,\n)\n\n\ndef parse_message(\n    message: str,\n    sender: str,\n    recent_context: list[dict] = None,  # last 5 messages for RSVP/modify context\n) -> ParsedMessage:\n    \"\"\"\n    Single LLM call: classify intent + extract entities.\n    \"\"\"\n    context_block = \"\"\n    if recent_context:\n        lines = [f\"[{m['sender']}]: {m['text']}\" for m in recent_context[-5:]]\n        context_block = f\"\\nRecent messages for context:\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=MODEL,\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Sender: {sender}\\nMessage: {message}{context_block}\"}\n        ],\n        response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n        temperature=0.0,\n        max_tokens=300,\n    )\n\n    raw_json = json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content)\n    parsed = ParsedMessage(\n        intent=raw_json[\"intent\"],\n        confidence=raw_json.get(\"confidence\", 0.5),\n        event=EventExtraction(**raw_json[\"event\"]) if raw_json.get(\"event\") else None,\n        query=QueryExtraction(**raw_json[\"query\"]) if raw_json.get(\"query\") else None,\n        ambiguities=raw_json.get(\"ambiguities\", []),\n        sender=sender,\n        raw_message=message,\n    )\n    return parsed\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Neo4j Event Schema\n\n### Node: `Event`\n\n```cypher\nCREATE (e:Event {\n    event_id: randomUUID(),\n    name: $name,\n    start_datetime: datetime($start),\n    end_datetime: datetime($end),\n    location: $location,\n    created_by: $sender,\n    created_at: datetime(),\n    source_message: $raw_message,\n    status: 'confirmed',        -- confirmed | cancelled | tentative\n    group_id: $signal_group_id\n})\n```\n\n### Node: `Participant`\n\n```cypher\nMERGE (p:Participant {name: $name, phone: $phone})\n```\n\n### Relationships\n\n```cypher\n(p:Participant)-[:ATTENDING {status: 'yes'|'no'|'maybe', responded_at: datetime()}]->(e:Event)\n(p:Participant)-[:CREATED]->(e:Event)\n(e:Event)-[:REMINDER {remind_at: datetime(), sent: false}]->(p:Participant)\n```\n\n### Indexes\n\n```cypher\nCREATE INDEX event_start IF NOT EXISTS FOR (e:Event) ON (e.start_datetime);\nCREATE INDEX event_status IF NOT EXISTS FOR (e:Event) ON (e.status);\nCREATE INDEX event_group IF NOT EXISTS FOR (e:Event) ON (e.group_id);\nCREATE CONSTRAINT event_id_unique IF NOT EXISTS FOR (e:Event) REQUIRE e.event_id IS UNIQUE;\nCREATE INDEX participant_phone IF NOT EXISTS FOR (p:Participant) ON (p.phone);\n```\n\n### Query: Events This Weekend\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event)\nWHERE e.start_datetime >= datetime($saturday_start)\n  AND e.start_datetime < datetime($monday_start)\n  AND e.status <> 'cancelled'\nOPTIONAL MATCH (p:Participant)-[a:ATTENDING]->(e)\nRETURN e.name, e.start_datetime, e.location,\n       collect({name: p.name, status: a.status}) AS attendees\nORDER BY e.start_datetime\n```\n\n### Query: Conflict Detection\n\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event)\nWHERE e.status <> 'cancelled'\n  AND e.start_datetime < datetime($proposed_end)\n  AND e.end_datetime > datetime($proposed_start)\nRETURN e.name, e.start_datetime, e.end_datetime\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Confirmation Flow\n\n### Decision Matrix\n\n| Condition | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| confidence >= 0.8 AND no ambiguities AND no conflicts | **Auto-confirm**: create event, send summary |\n| confidence >= 0.8 AND has conflict | **Warn + confirm**: show conflict, ask to proceed |\n| confidence >= 0.6 AND < 0.8 | **Ask for confirmation**: show parsed interpretation, wait for yes/no |\n| confidence < 0.6 | **Ask for clarification**: \"I wasn't sure -- did you mean to create an event?\" |\n| Any ambiguities present | **Ask for clarification** on the specific ambiguity |\n\n### Confirmation Message Templates\n\n#### Auto-confirmed (high confidence, no issues)\n\n```\n[Calendar] Got it!\n  Dinner at Mario's\n  Friday, March 13 at 7:00 PM\n  Location: Mario's\n  Duration: 2 hours\nReact with a thumbs up to join, thumbs down to skip.\n```\n\n#### Needs confirmation (medium confidence or ambiguity)\n\n```\n[Calendar] I think you want to create:\n  Dinner at Mario's\n  Friday, March 13 at 7:00 PM\n  Location: Mario's\nDoes that look right? Reply \"yes\" to confirm or correct me.\n```\n\n#### Conflict detected\n\n```\n[Calendar] Heads up -- you already have:\n  Game Night at 6:00 PM - 8:00 PM\nThe new event would overlap:\n  Dinner at Mario's at 7:00 PM\nCreate anyway? Reply \"yes\" to confirm.\n```\n\n#### Clarification needed (low confidence)\n\n```\n[Calendar] Not sure I caught that -- did you want to schedule something?\nIf so, try: \"Dinner at Mario's, Friday at 7pm\"\n```\n\n#### RSVP confirmation\n\n```\n[Calendar] Marked you as attending: Dinner at Mario's (Fri 7 PM)\n  Attending: Alex, Jordan, you\n  Not attending: Sam\n```\n\n### Confirmation State Machine\n\nWhen awaiting confirmation, the system enters a per-user pending state:\n\n```python\n# In-memory (or Redis if needed later)\npending_confirmations: dict[str, PendingConfirmation] = {}\n\nclass PendingConfirmation(BaseModel):\n    user_phone: str\n    resolved_event: ResolvedEvent\n    created_at: datetime\n    expires_at: datetime  # auto-expire after 10 minutes\n\n# Next message from same user is checked against pending:\n# - \"yes\", \"y\", \"yep\", \"do it\" -> confirm and create\n# - \"no\", \"nah\", \"cancel\" -> discard\n# - anything else -> treat as new message (pending expires)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. Error Handling\n\n### Error: Date is ambiguous\n\n**Trigger:** `date_text` = \"next week\", \"sometime soon\", \"later\"\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] When exactly? \"Next week\" could be any day.\nTry something like \"Tuesday at 6pm\" or \"next Saturday afternoon\"\n```\n\n**Implementation:** The resolver returns `is_ambiguous: true`. The confirmation flow routes to clarification.\n\n### Error: No event name detected\n\n**Trigger:** \"Let's do something Friday\" -- has a date but no name.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Friday at 7:00 PM -- what should I call this event?\n```\n\n**Implementation:** If `event.name` is null or generic (\"something\", \"thing\", \"stuff\"), prompt for a name. Auto-generate from location if available (\"Mario's on Friday\").\n\n**Fallback name generation:**\n```python\ndef generate_event_name(event: EventExtraction) -> str:\n    if event.name and event.name.lower() not in (\"something\", \"thing\", \"stuff\", \"it\"):\n        return event.name\n    if event.location:\n        return event.location  # \"Mario's\" becomes the event name\n    return \"Unnamed Event\"  # Last resort, will prompt user\n```\n\n### Error: Multiple events in one message\n\n**Trigger:** \"Brunch Sunday at 11 and then hiking at 2\"\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] I found 2 events:\n  1. Brunch -- Sunday at 11:00 AM\n  2. Hiking -- Sunday at 2:00 PM\nCreate both? Reply \"yes\" or specify which one.\n```\n\n**Implementation:** The LLM prompt says to return the primary event and note others in `ambiguities`. For multi-event detection, we check the ambiguities array for patterns like \"second event\" or \"also mentioned\". In practice, the LLM can be prompted to return an array -- but the MVP handles one event per message and flags the rest.\n\n### Error: Conflicting times\n\n**Trigger:** \"Dinner at 7 and also at 8\" or modification that contradicts itself.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] I see two times mentioned: 7:00 PM and 8:00 PM.\nWhich one did you mean?\n```\n\n**Implementation:** If `date_text` contains multiple parseable times (dateparser returns different results for substrings), flag as ambiguous.\n\n### Error: Reference event not found (RSVP/modify/cancel)\n\n**Trigger:** \"Cancel the dinner\" but no recent dinner event exists.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] I couldn't find a \"dinner\" event coming up.\nUpcoming events:\n  - Game Night (Fri 6 PM)\n  - Hiking (Sun 9 AM)\nWhich one did you mean?\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n```cypher\nMATCH (e:Event)\nWHERE e.status <> 'cancelled'\n  AND e.start_datetime > datetime()\nRETURN e.name, e.start_datetime\nORDER BY e.start_datetime\nLIMIT 5\n```\n\nFuzzy match `reference_event` against returned names using simple substring/Levenshtein.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Example Message-to-Output Mappings\n\n### Example 1: Standard event creation\n\n**Message:** `\"Dinner at Mario's on Friday at 7pm\"`\n**Sender:** Alex\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"Dinner at Mario's\",\n    \"date_text\": \"Friday at 7pm\",\n    \"location\": \"Mario's\",\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Resolved:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Dinner at Mario's\",\n  \"start_datetime\": \"2026-03-13T19:00:00-08:00\",\n  \"end_datetime\": \"2026-03-13T21:00:00-08:00\",\n  \"location\": \"Mario's\",\n  \"participants\": [\"Alex\"],\n  \"created_by\": \"Alex\"\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Auto-confirm. Confidence >= 0.8, no ambiguities.\n\n---\n\n### Example 2: Minimal/informal event\n\n**Message:** `\"hike sat morning?\"`\n**Sender:** Jordan\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.82,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"Hike\",\n    \"date_text\": \"sat morning\",\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"No location specified\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Resolved:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Hike\",\n  \"start_datetime\": \"2026-03-07T09:00:00-08:00\",\n  \"end_datetime\": \"2026-03-07T11:00:00-08:00\",\n  \"location\": null,\n  \"participants\": [\"Jordan\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Auto-confirm (confidence >= 0.8). Morning for \"hike\" resolves to 9 AM via AM/PM heuristic.\n\n---\n\n### Example 3: Event with participants\n\n**Message:** `\"Board game night at my place next Saturday 6pm, with Sam, Liz, and Chris\"`\n**Sender:** Alex\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"Board game night\",\n    \"date_text\": \"next Saturday 6pm\",\n    \"location\": \"Alex's place\",\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [\"Sam\", \"Liz\", \"Chris\"],\n    \"reference_event\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Resolved:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Board game night\",\n  \"start_datetime\": \"2026-03-14T18:00:00-08:00\",\n  \"end_datetime\": \"2026-03-14T20:00:00-08:00\",\n  \"location\": \"Alex's place\",\n  \"participants\": [\"Alex\", \"Sam\", \"Liz\", \"Chris\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Auto-confirm. \"my place\" resolved to \"Alex's place\" using sender context.\n\n---\n\n### Example 4: Event query\n\n**Message:** `\"What are we doing this weekend?\"`\n**Sender:** Sam\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_query\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.92,\n  \"event\": null,\n  \"query\": {\n    \"time_range\": \"this weekend\",\n    \"filter\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Query Neo4j for events between Saturday 00:00 and Monday 00:00. Return list.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] This weekend:\n  Sat 9:00 AM - Hike (Jordan)\n  Sat 6:00 PM - Board game night at Alex's (Alex, Sam, Liz, Chris)\n  Nothing on Sunday yet!\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 5: RSVP yes\n\n**Message:** `\"I'm in for the game night\"`\n**Sender:** Taylor\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_rsvp_yes\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.90,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": null,\n    \"date_text\": null,\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"game night\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Fuzzy-match \"game night\" against upcoming events. Find \"Board game night\". Create `ATTENDING` relationship with status `yes`.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] You're in for Board game night (Sat 6 PM at Alex's)\n  Attending: Alex, Sam, Liz, Chris, you\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 6: RSVP no with context\n\n**Message:** `\"can't make it saturday, have fun tho\"`\n**Sender:** Sam\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_rsvp_no\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.78,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": null,\n    \"date_text\": \"saturday\",\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"Multiple events on Saturday - unclear which one\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Two events on Saturday. Ask for clarification.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] You have 2 things on Saturday:\n  1. Hike (9 AM)\n  2. Board game night (6 PM)\nSkipping both, or just one?\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 7: Event modification\n\n**Message:** `\"actually let's push dinner to 8 instead\"`\n**Sender:** Alex\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_modify\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.85,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": null,\n    \"date_text\": \"8\",\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"dinner\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Find most recent upcoming \"dinner\" event. Change start_datetime to 8 PM (same day). Notify group.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Updated: Dinner at Mario's\n  Was: Friday at 7:00 PM\n  Now: Friday at 8:00 PM\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 8: Cancellation\n\n**Message:** `\"scratch the hiking trip, weather looks bad\"`\n**Sender:** Jordan\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_cancel\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.92,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": null,\n    \"date_text\": null,\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"hiking trip\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Match \"hiking trip\" to \"Hike\" event. Set `status: 'cancelled'`. Notify group.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Cancelled: Hike (Sat 9 AM)\nReason: weather looks bad\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 9: Reminder request\n\n**Message:** `\"remind me about the game night 2 hours before\"`\n**Sender:** Liz\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_remind\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.90,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": null,\n    \"date_text\": \"2 hours before\",\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"game night\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Find \"Board game night\" (Sat 6 PM). Create reminder for 4 PM. Store as `REMINDER` relationship.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Reminder set: Board game night\n  I'll ping you Saturday at 4:00 PM (2 hours before)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 10: Not calendar-related\n\n**Message:** `\"lmaooo did you guys see that video\"`\n**Sender:** Chris\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"not_calendar\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.98,\n  \"event\": null,\n  \"query\": null,\n  \"ambiguities\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Ignore. No response sent.\n\n---\n\n### Example 11: Ambiguous date\n\n**Message:** `\"let's get drinks next week\"`\n**Sender:** Taylor\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.75,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"Drinks\",\n    \"date_text\": \"next week\",\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"'next week' is vague - which day?\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Confidence < 0.8 and ambiguity flagged. Ask for clarification.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Drinks next week -- which day works?\nPick a day and time and I'll set it up.\n```\n\n---\n\n### Example 12: Multiple events in one message\n\n**Message:** `\"brunch at 11 on Sunday then movies at 3\"`\n**Sender:** Alex\n\n```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.88,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"Brunch\",\n    \"date_text\": \"11 on Sunday\",\n    \"location\": null,\n    \"duration_minutes\": null,\n    \"participants\": [],\n    \"reference_event\": null\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"Also mentioned: movies at 3 PM on Sunday\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Action:** Create primary event (brunch). Flag the second event. Ask about it.\n\n**Response:**\n```\n[Calendar] Created: Brunch\n  Sunday at 11:00 AM, 2 hours\n\nAlso noticed: Movies at 3:00 PM on Sunday -- want me to add that too?\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. Context Window Management\n\nThe LLM needs recent chat context for RSVP and modification messages. Strategy:\n\n```python\n# Store last N messages per group in a rolling buffer\n# Only send the last 5 messages as context to the LLM\n# Only include messages from the last 30 minutes (recency filter)\n\nclass MessageBuffer:\n    def __init__(self, max_size: int = 20):\n        self.messages: list[dict] = []\n        self.max_size = max_size\n\n    def add(self, sender: str, text: str, timestamp: datetime):\n        self.messages.append({\"sender\": sender, \"text\": text, \"ts\": timestamp})\n        if len(self.messages) > self.max_size:\n            self.messages.pop(0)\n\n    def recent(self, minutes: int = 30, limit: int = 5) -> list[dict]:\n        cutoff = datetime.now() - timedelta(minutes=minutes)\n        recent = [m for m in self.messages if m[\"ts\"] > cutoff]\n        return recent[-limit:]\n```\n\nThis is critical for RSVP resolution. \"I'm in\" means nothing without knowing what event was just proposed.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Full Pipeline Flow (Pseudocode)\n\n```python\nasync def handle_signal_message(raw_msg: dict):\n    text = raw_msg[\"message\"]\n    sender = raw_msg[\"sender\"]         # phone number\n    sender_name = lookup_name(sender)  # from contacts/Neo4j\n    group_id = raw_msg[\"group_id\"]\n\n    # 1. Add to context buffer\n    buffer = get_buffer(group_id)\n    buffer.add(sender_name, text, datetime.now())\n\n    # 2. Check if this is a confirmation response to a pending event\n    pending = pending_confirmations.get(sender)\n    if pending and not pending.expired():\n        if is_affirmative(text):\n            create_event_in_neo4j(pending.resolved_event)\n            send_signal(group_id, format_confirmed(pending.resolved_event))\n            del pending_confirmations[sender]\n            return\n        elif is_negative(text):\n            send_signal(group_id, \"OK, cancelled.\")\n            del pending_confirmations[sender]\n            return\n        # else: fall through, treat as new message\n\n    # 3. Classify + extract (single LLM call)\n    parsed = parse_message(text, sender_name, buffer.recent())\n\n    # 4. Route by intent\n    if parsed.intent == Intent.NOT_CALENDAR:\n        return  # ignore\n\n    if parsed.intent == Intent.EVENT_QUERY:\n        results = query_events(parsed.query)\n        send_signal(group_id, format_query_results(results))\n        return\n\n    if parsed.intent == Intent.EVENT_CREATE:\n        # 5. Resolve date/time\n        resolved = resolve_datetime(parsed.event.date_text)\n\n        if resolved[\"start\"] is None or resolved[\"is_ambiguous\"]:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_clarification(parsed, resolved))\n            return\n\n        # 6. Build event\n        event = ResolvedEvent(\n            name=generate_event_name(parsed.event),\n            start_datetime=resolved[\"start\"],\n            end_datetime=resolved[\"end\"] or resolved[\"start\"] + DEFAULT_DURATION,\n            location=parsed.event.location,\n            participants=[sender_name] + parsed.event.participants,\n            created_by=sender_name,\n            source_message=text,\n            confidence=parsed.confidence,\n        )\n\n        # 7. Check conflicts\n        conflicts = check_conflicts(event.start_datetime, event.end_datetime)\n\n        # 8. Confirm or create\n        if parsed.confidence >= 0.8 and not conflicts and not parsed.ambiguities:\n            create_event_in_neo4j(event)\n            send_signal(group_id, format_confirmed(event))\n        elif conflicts:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_conflict(event, conflicts))\n            pending_confirmations[sender] = PendingConfirmation(\n                user_phone=sender, resolved_event=event,\n                created_at=datetime.now(),\n                expires_at=datetime.now() + timedelta(minutes=10),\n            )\n        else:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_needs_confirmation(event))\n            pending_confirmations[sender] = PendingConfirmation(\n                user_phone=sender, resolved_event=event,\n                created_at=datetime.now(),\n                expires_at=datetime.now() + timedelta(minutes=10),\n            )\n\n    if parsed.intent in (Intent.RSVP_YES, Intent.RSVP_NO, Intent.RSVP_MAYBE):\n        matched_event = fuzzy_match_event(parsed.event.reference_event)\n        if matched_event:\n            update_rsvp(sender_name, matched_event, parsed.intent)\n            send_signal(group_id, format_rsvp(sender_name, matched_event, parsed.intent))\n        else:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_event_not_found(parsed.event.reference_event))\n\n    if parsed.intent == Intent.EVENT_MODIFY:\n        matched_event = fuzzy_match_event(parsed.event.reference_event)\n        if matched_event:\n            new_time = resolve_datetime(parsed.event.date_text)\n            update_event(matched_event, new_time)\n            send_signal(group_id, format_modification(matched_event, new_time))\n        else:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_event_not_found(parsed.event.reference_event))\n\n    if parsed.intent == Intent.EVENT_CANCEL:\n        matched_event = fuzzy_match_event(parsed.event.reference_event)\n        if matched_event:\n            cancel_event(matched_event)\n            send_signal(group_id, format_cancellation(matched_event))\n        else:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_event_not_found(parsed.event.reference_event))\n\n    if parsed.intent == Intent.EVENT_REMIND:\n        matched_event = fuzzy_match_event(parsed.event.reference_event)\n        if matched_event:\n            remind_at = compute_reminder_time(matched_event, parsed.event.date_text)\n            set_reminder(sender_name, matched_event, remind_at)\n            send_signal(group_id, format_reminder_set(matched_event, remind_at))\n        else:\n            send_signal(group_id, format_event_not_found(parsed.event.reference_event))\n```\n\n---\n\n## 13. Reminder Delivery\n\nReminders are stored as relationships in Neo4j and checked by a cron job:\n\n```python\n# reminder_worker.py -- runs every minute via launchd or cron\ndef check_reminders():\n    driver = get_driver()\n    with driver.session() as session:\n        result = session.run(\"\"\"\n            MATCH (e:Event)-[r:REMINDER]->(p:Participant)\n            WHERE r.remind_at <= datetime()\n              AND r.sent = false\n              AND e.status <> 'cancelled'\n            SET r.sent = true\n            RETURN e.name, e.start_datetime, e.location, p.phone, p.name\n        \"\"\")\n        for record in result:\n            send_signal_dm(\n                record[\"p.phone\"],\n                f\"Reminder: {record['e.name']} at \"\n                f\"{record['e.start_datetime'].strftime('%I:%M %p')} \"\n                f\"{'at ' + record['e.location'] if record['e.location'] else ''}\"\n            )\n    driver.close()\n```\n\n---\n\n## 14. Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit tests for date resolution\n\n```python\n# test_resolver.py\ndef test_friday_resolves_to_next_friday():\n    ref = datetime(2026, 3, 6, 10, 0)  # Friday\n    result = resolve_datetime(\"Friday at 7pm\", ref)\n    assert result[\"start\"].weekday() == 4\n    assert result[\"start\"].hour == 19\n    assert result[\"start\"] > ref\n\ndef test_this_weekend():\n    ref = datetime(2026, 3, 4, 10, 0)  # Wednesday\n    result = resolve_datetime(\"this weekend\", ref)\n    assert result[\"start\"].weekday() == 5  # Saturday\n\ndef test_bare_3_is_pm():\n    ref = datetime(2026, 3, 6, 10, 0)\n    result = resolve_datetime(\"March 15 at 3\", ref)\n    assert result[\"start\"].hour == 15\n\ndef test_next_week_is_ambiguous():\n    result = resolve_datetime(\"next week\")\n    assert result[\"is_ambiguous\"] is True\n```\n\n### Integration tests with real LLM calls\n\n```python\n# test_classifier.py (hits OpenRouter, run sparingly)\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_dinner_classified_as_event_create():\n    result = parse_message(\"Dinner at Mario's Friday 7pm\", \"Alex\")\n    assert result.intent == Intent.EVENT_CREATE\n    assert result.event.location == \"Mario's\"\n    assert result.confidence >= 0.8\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_lol_classified_as_not_calendar():\n    result = parse_message(\"lmaooo did you see that\", \"Chris\")\n    assert result.intent == Intent.NOT_CALENDAR\n```\n\n---\n\n## 15. Failure Modes and Mitigations\n\n| Failure | Mitigation |\n|---------|------------|\n| OpenRouter API down | Queue messages, process when API returns. Set 5s timeout. |\n| LLM returns invalid JSON | Wrap in try/except, retry once. If still invalid, ignore message. |\n| Neo4j down | Log to filesystem, backfill when Neo4j recovers (same pattern as `neo4j-state-sync.py`). |\n| signal-cli crashes | Launchd KeepAlive restarts it. Messages buffer in Signal servers. |\n| Duplicate event creation | Hash `name + start_datetime + group_id`, check before INSERT. |\n| User sends 50 messages in a row | Rate limit: max 5 calendar operations per user per minute. |\n| Timezone confusion | All datetimes stored as UTC in Neo4j, displayed in `America/Los_Angeles`. |\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe pipeline uses a **single LLM call** (Claude Haiku via OpenRouter, ~$0.45/month) for classification and entity extraction, **dateparser** for deterministic date/time resolution, and **Neo4j** for event storage with proper indexing. The confirmation flow auto-confirms high-confidence parses and asks for clarification on ambiguous ones. The system handles 9 intent types, maintains a rolling context buffer for RSVP resolution, and stores reminders as graph relationships checked by a minute-interval cron job.\n\nKey design decisions:\n1. **One LLM call, not two** -- classification and extraction in a single request\n2. **LLM for semantics, dateparser for dates** -- each tool used for what it does best\n3. **Auto-confirm obvious events** -- don't make users confirm \"Dinner at Mario's Friday 7pm\"\n4. **10-minute confirmation timeout** -- pending confirmations expire to avoid stale state\n5. **Fuzzy event matching** for RSVP/modify/cancel -- \"game night\" matches \"Board game night\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772866306696}}
{"type":"message","id":"77567f56","parentId":"64f817c7","timestamp":"2026-03-07T06:51:46.741Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_10877325754d4d4383d47001","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nCalendar Parser - LLM classification + date/time resolution for Signal calendar\n\nUses a single LLM call for intent classification + entity extraction,\nthen dateparser for deterministic datetime resolution.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom zoneinfo import ZoneInfo\nfrom typing import Optional, List, Dict, Any\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field\n\nimport dateparser\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n# Load OpenRouter API key from env\nENV_FILE = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/config/.env\")\nif os.path.exists(ENV_FILE):\n    with open(ENV_FILE) as f:\n        for line in f:\n            if line.startswith(\"OPENROUTER_API_KEY\"):\n                os.environ.setdefault(\"OPENROUTER_API_KEY\", line.strip().split(\"=\", 1)[1])\n\nOPENROUTER_API_KEY = os.getenv(\"OPENROUTER_API_KEY\")\nMODEL = \"anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku\"\n\nLOCAL_TZ = ZoneInfo(\"America/New_York\")\nDEFAULT_DURATION = timedelta(hours=2)\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# Intent Types\n# =============================================================================\n\nclass Intent(str, Enum):\n    EVENT_CREATE = \"event_create\"\n    EVENT_QUERY = \"event_query\"\n    RSVP_YES = \"event_rsvp_yes\"\n    RSVP_NO = \"event_rsvp_no\"\n    RSVP_MAYBE = \"event_rsvp_maybe\"\n    EVENT_MODIFY = \"event_modify\"\n    EVENT_CANCEL = \"event_cancel\"\n    EVENT_REMIND = \"event_remind\"\n    NOT_CALENDAR = \"not_calendar\"\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# Pydantic Models\n# =============================================================================\n\nclass EventExtraction(BaseModel):\n    name: Optional[str] = None\n    date_text: Optional[str] = None\n    location: Optional[str] = None\n    duration_minutes: Optional[int] = None\n    participants: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    reference_event: Optional[str] = None\n\n\nclass QueryExtraction(BaseModel):\n    time_range: Optional[str] = None\n    filter: Optional[str] = None\n\n\nclass ParsedMessage(BaseModel):\n    intent: Intent\n    confidence: float = Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    event: Optional[EventExtraction] = None\n    query: Optional[QueryExtraction] = None\n    ambiguities: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    sender: str = \"\"\n    raw_message: str = \"\"\n    timestamp: datetime = Field(default_factory=lambda: datetime.now(LOCAL_TZ))\n\n\nclass ResolvedEvent(BaseModel):\n    name: str\n    start_datetime: datetime\n    end_datetime: datetime\n    location: Optional[str] = None\n    participants: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    reminders: List[datetime] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    created_by: str = \"\"\n    source_message: str = \"\"\n    confidence: float = 1.0\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# LLM System Prompt\n# =============================================================================\n\nSYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a calendar assistant parsing messages from a group chat.\n\nGiven a message and recent chat context, respond with JSON only. No explanation.\n\nSchema:\n{\n  \"intent\": \"event_create\" | \"event_query\" | \"event_rsvp_yes\" | \"event_rsvp_no\" |\n            \"event_rsvp_maybe\" | \"event_modify\" | \"event_cancel\" | \"event_remind\" |\n            \"not_calendar\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.0-1.0,\n  \"event\": {\n    \"name\": \"string or null\",\n    \"date_text\": \"string or null\",\n    \"location\": \"string or null\",\n    \"duration_minutes\": int or null,\n    \"participants\": [\"string\"] or [],\n    \"reference_event\": \"string or null\"\n  },\n  \"query\": {\n    \"time_range\": \"string or null\",\n    \"filter\": \"string or null\"\n  },\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"string\"]\n}\n\nRules:\n- \"I'm in\" / \"count me in\" with no context = not_calendar (need reference event)\n- \"I'm in\" following an event creation = event_rsvp_yes referencing that event\n- If the message contains multiple events, return the primary one and note others in ambiguities\n- confidence < 0.6 = flag for confirmation\n- Default duration is null (caller will apply 2-hour default)\n- Participants are first names only as mentioned in the message\n- For RSVP/modify/cancel, reference_event should match the most recent relevant event name\n\"\"\"\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# LLM Classification\n# =============================================================================\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=\"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\",\n    api_key=OPENROUTER_API_KEY,\n)\n\n\ndef parse_message(\n    message: str,\n    sender: str,\n    recent_context: List[Dict] = None,\n) -> ParsedMessage:\n    \"\"\"\n    Single LLM call: classify intent + extract entities.\n\n    Args:\n        message: The message text to parse\n        sender: Name or phone of sender\n        recent_context: List of recent messages for context (last 5)\n\n    Returns:\n        ParsedMessage with intent, confidence, and extracted entities\n    \"\"\"\n    context_block = \"\"\n    if recent_context:\n        lines = [f\"[{m['sender']}]: {m['text']}\" for m in recent_context[-5:]]\n        context_block = \"\\nRecent messages for context:\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n    try:\n        response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=MODEL,\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Sender: {sender}\\nMessage: {message}{context_block}\"}\n            ],\n            response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n            temperature=0.0,\n            max_tokens=300,\n            timeout=10.0,\n        )\n\n        raw_json = json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content)\n\n        event_data = raw_json.get(\"event\")\n        event = EventExtraction(**event_data) if event_data else None\n\n        query_data = raw_json.get(\"query\")\n        query = QueryExtraction(**query_data) if query_data else None\n\n        parsed = ParsedMessage(\n            intent=Intent(raw_json[\"intent\"]),\n            confidence=float(raw_json.get(\"confidence\", 0.5)),\n            event=event,\n            query=query,\n            ambiguities=raw_json.get(\"ambiguities\", []),\n            sender=sender,\n            raw_message=message,\n        )\n        return parsed\n    except Exception as e:\n        # Fallback: return NOT_CALENDAR\n        return ParsedMessage(\n            intent=Intent.NOT_CALENDAR,\n            confidence=0.0,\n            sender=sender,\n            raw_message=message,\n            ambiguities=[f\"Parse error: {str(e)}\"]\n        )\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# Date/Time Resolution\n# =============================================================================\n\ndef _is_weekend_reference(text: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if text refers to 'this weekend'.\"\"\"\n    return \"weekend\" in text.lower()\n\n\ndef _next_weekday(dt: datetime, weekday: int) -> datetime:\n    \"\"\"Get the next occurrence of a weekday (0=Monday, 6=Sunday).\"\"\"\n    days_ahead = weekday - dt.weekday()\n    if days_ahead <= 0:\n        days_ahead += 7\n    return dt + timedelta(days=days_ahead)\n\n\ndef _detect_ambiguity(date_text: str, parsed: datetime, reference: datetime) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Detect if the date resolution is ambiguous.\"\"\"\n    text_lower = date_text.lower().strip()\n\n    # Known ambiguous patterns\n    ambiguous_patterns = [\n        \"next week\", \"sometime\", \"later\", \"soon\", \"whenever\",\n        \"one day\", \"some day\", \"maybe\", \"perhaps\"\n    ]\n\n    return any(p in text_lower for p in ambiguous_patterns)\n\n\ndef _generate_alternatives(date_text: str, primary: datetime) -> List[datetime]:\n    \"\"\"Generate alternative interpretations for ambiguous dates.\"\"\"\n    # For now, just return empty - could be enhanced\n    return []\n\n\ndef apply_ampm_heuristic(hour: int, event_name: str = \"\") -> int:\n    \"\"\"For bare hour numbers, infer AM/PM from event context.\"\"\"\n    morning_events = {\"breakfast\", \"brunch\", \"coffee\", \"run\", \"hike\", \"yoga\", \"morning\"}\n    name_lower = (event_name or \"\").lower()\n\n    if any(kw in name_lower for kw in morning_events):\n        return hour  # Keep as AM\n\n    # Social default: bare hours 1-6 are PM\n    if 1 <= hour <= 6:\n        return hour + 12\n\n    # 7-11: default PM for social, unless morning keyword\n    if 7 <= hour <= 11:\n        return hour\n\n    return hour\n\n\ndef resolve_datetime(\n    date_text: str,\n    reference_time: datetime = None,\n    event_name: str = None\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Resolve a date string to an absolute datetime.\n\n    Args:\n        date_text: The raw date text from LLM extraction\n        reference_time: The reference time for resolution (default: now)\n        event_name: Event name for AM/PM heuristics\n\n    Returns:\n        Dict with start, end, is_ambiguous, interpretation, alternatives\n    \"\"\"\n    if reference_time is None:\n        reference_time = datetime.now(LOCAL_TZ)\n\n    if not date_text:\n        return {\n            \"start\": None,\n            \"end\": None,\n            \"is_ambiguous\": True,\n            \"interpretation\": \"No date specified\",\n            \"alternatives\": []\n        }\n\n    # Special pattern: \"this weekend\"\n    if _is_weekend_reference(date_text):\n        sat = _next_weekday(reference_time, 5)  # Saturday\n        sun = sat + timedelta(days=1)\n